# Architect — mcp/qdrant-explorer

## Role in architecture

This MCP server is a **DX tool** — not a production service. It exposes Qdrant read operations to AI agents (Claude Code, Gemini CLI, Codex, Cursor) for RAG evaluation and debugging.

## Contract

The server's MCP manifest (tool names + parameter schemas + docstrings) is the contract. Any change to:
- Tool name → breaking for any agent that references the tool by name
- Parameter schema → may break existing agent prompts
- Return type → may break agent parsing

## Design rules

- Add tools that serve distinct debugging use cases — do not add tools that duplicate existing ones
- Tools must be stateless — no session state between calls
- Read-only only — never expose write operations to Qdrant

## When to write an ADR

- Adding a new tool category (e.g., write operations, cross-collection queries)
- Changing the authentication model
- Adding a new external dependency
